      "content": "that's a great start, it definitely has that academic weight i'm looking for. can you expand on that? specifically, i want to address the common rebuttal about \"meritocracy.\" i want to show that the idea of meritocracy is actually just a way to justify existing racial wealth gaps rather than being a real thing. can you write a section that basically dismantles the meritocracy argument as a fallacy used to protect the status quo?",
